parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the rear brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels spongy or fades
ABS light illuminates on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal fade can cause extended stopping distance, increasing the risk of accidents and collisions.
The failure of the ignition module can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off without warning, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates and stalls without warning
the vehicle restarts itself but shuts off again

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ignition switch can cause all electrical components to fail, leading to a loss of visibility and increased risk of accidents.
An electrical system fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire under the driver's floorboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the oil pan can cause oil leakage, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially, engine failure. In extreme cases, it can also cause a fire in the engine compartment.
symptoms: Oil leakage from the underside of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss. It can also pose a risk to the safety of the occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Flames or smoke coming from the engine compartment
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard.
